I have seen this image circulate a bit here and on /fit/, presented as a "regular man" from the past.

The man, we can easily see, is actually a bodybuilder. Such a chest can not develop without specific pectoral exercise, this is not a "natural" physique.

Natural movements like chopping wood, carrying heavy objects etc. almost never target the chest. This is also why first bodybuilders looked at chest training as feminine (aka artificial*). Let's not lie to oursevles, our grandpas werent bodybuilders

*there were other reasons too
